I would expect to get an unauthorized status or something like that, indicating the request is rejected, instead of a 500.

Also I wouldn't expect the need to add authentication, since a successful policy validation makes the request work like a charm.
If it was as simple as adding 

`builder.Services.AddAuthentication();`
